I"‰<ul>
  <li>This is straightforward. I just use the <a href="https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/remote/ssh">editing over ssh feature</a> to enter the SSH connection command (<code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">ssh -i ~/.ssh/wsl2.pub roland@somehost.tcp.ngrok.io -p &lt;someport&gt;</code>) in Visual Studio Code (and of course I could always use emacs to edit over ssh which Iâ€™ve done for decades!).</li>
  <li>And I use the terminal feature to trigger a jekyll rebuild and then <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">surge</code> to upload my blog and git all in Visual Studio Codeâ€™s terminal.</li>
  <li>Super geeky :-) but then I can edit any of my 5 laptops !</li>
